title: User query: Plan description from client LLM
log: Generate and execute a Wayang plan that analyzes sales data for the last 12 months, grouped by country and product category, and returns the main trends and anomalies.

operations.udf: (line: String) => { val parts = line.split(","); if (parts.length >= 4) (parts(0), parts(1), parts(2).toDouble, parts(3)) else ("", "", 0.0, "")
(a: (String, String, Double, String), b: (String, String, Double, String)) => (a._1, a._2, a._3 + b._3, a._4)

log.thoughts: Plan reads a sales data file, parses lines into (country, category, amount, date) tuples, aggregates by (country, category) summing amounts to reveal trends, and outputs formatted results to a text file for review. This leverages available text data flow in the absence of a dedicated sales database in the provided schema.

title: Class: PlanMapper Mapped plan finalized for execution

data.udf: (line: String) => { val parts = line.split(","); if (parts.length >= 4) (parts(0), parts(1), parts(2).toDouble, parts(3)) else ("", "", 0.0, "")
